		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Inescapable Grasp",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "passive"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>Your grasp has a supernatural quality to it, preventing your foes from easily escaping—with or without magical assistance. If a creature you have @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed} attempts to use a teleportation spell or effect, it must succeed at a @Check[flat|dc:15] or the spell fails. If a creature you have grabbed attempts to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.SkZAQRkLLkmBQNB9]{Escape} while under the effect of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.aqRYNoSvxsVfqglH]{Unfettered Movement} or a similar effect, it must succeed at a @Check[flat|dc:15] or be forced to roll the Escape attempt normally, rather than automatically succeeding.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feat-effects.Item.dDdxIy1bAvwfuhx0]{Effect: Inescapable Grasp}</p>",
